### Wed 2026-03-19 — OpenServ Trigger URL Discovery
**Source: memory/2026-03-19.md**

Key technical discovery: the MCP URL Jean had configured returned 404 when called with a raw HTTP POST — because MCP requires specific transport negotiation (stdio/SSE/HTTP), not raw JSON-RPC. This was the MCP dead end Jean mentioned as "the one that surprised me most."

The pivot: switch to OpenServ's webhook-based manual trigger. Jean configured the workflow with a `{promptResponse}` field on the manual trigger. The backend was refactored to send `{ agentResponse }` in the POST body.

PR #2 opened to wire the pasted agent response → backend POST → OpenServ trigger. The trigger URL was still missing at this point — waiting on Jean to provide it.

Three test profiles were prepared to validate the trigger:
1. Smart Contract Auditor — Solidity, EVM, security analysis
2. Full-Stack TypeScript Dev — React, Next.js, Tailwind, PostgreSQL
3. AI/ML Specialist — PyTorch, TensorFlow, NLP, computer vision

Jean configured the OpenServ workflow: Manual Trigger → General Assistant → expanded Research Agent (Upwork, Fiverr, Freelancer, TopTal, and 6 more platforms).

